<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[344,491,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fiuzai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[344,491,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Balera fiuzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[500,592,152,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[500,592,152,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has the pygofer, style and aedeagus, the last very superficially, similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Freytag" authorityName="Freytag" box="[256,466,189,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myersi">
<emphasis box="[256,367,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">B. myersi</emphasis>
Freytag
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from that species by the larger size of the posterodorsal projection of the pygofer, the narrower aedeagal atrial region and sinuate stem (in lateral view), and the number and position of aedeagal apical processes (Freytag 
<number box="[673,733,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" value="1992.0">1992</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,296,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named in honor of Prof. Paulo Sérgio Fiuza Ferreira, PhD. (Departamento de Biologia Animal da Universidade Federal de Viçosa), in recognition of his contributions to entomology.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
